div.p:
Revolutionary War material worthy of note includes the Index to the Official Register of Officers and Men of New Jersey in the Revolutionary War, compiled in 1941 by the Historical Records Survey of New Jersey . It greatly facilitates the use of the volume which it indexes. Other volumes are: Loyalists of North Carolina during the Revolution, by R. O. DeMond, 1940;
Delaware Continentals, 1776–1783, by C. L. Ward, 1941;
Delaware Loyalists, by H. B. Hancock, 1940.
